<h2>Professional background</h2>
<ul>
<li>2007-2009&nbsp;Norway’s chief negotiator under the United Nations climate change negotiations, Ministry of Environment </li>
<li>2003-2007&nbsp;Senior Adviser with responsibility for the development of Norway’s cap and trade system (climate change), Ministry of Environment </li>
<li>2000-2003 Vice-President and Judge, The Labour Court </li>
<li>1997-2000&nbsp;Agent, Attorney General of Civil Affairs </li>
<li>1995-1997&nbsp;Corporate Councellor, Aker Oil and Gas Technology PLC </li>
<li>1994-1995&nbsp;Political Secretary to Commissioner for Finance and Planning Rune Bjerke, Oslo City Government </li>
<li>1987-1994 Senior Executive Officer/Adviser, Legislation Department, Ministry of Justice </li>
<li>1992&nbsp;Visiting researcher, Institute for Social Research. </li>
<li>1987- 2006 Part-time teacher and external examiner (administrative law), University of Oslo. </li>
<li>1984-1985 Scientific Assistant (maritime law), University of Oslo. </li>
<li>1981-1982 Legal consultant (women’s rights), University of Oslo. </li></ul>
<h2>Education</h2>
<ul>
<li>1996&nbsp;Barrister training for lawyers (mandatory) </li>
<li>1990&nbsp;Masters Degree (LLM), International Law, London School of Economics and Political Science&nbsp; </li>
<li>1987&nbsp;&nbsp;Bachelor of law, University of Oslo1984&nbsp;&nbsp;Summer University "Introduction to English Law", University of London. </li>
<li>1980&nbsp;Studies within Italian film and art history, Institute for foreign students, University of Firenze.</li></ul>
